complaints.summary: I AM A 78 YEAR OLD WOMAN DEALING WITH MALES AT ACURA/HONDA WHO HAVE DONE NOTHING BUT RUN AROUND AND STALL. I HAVE HAD TWO TERRIBLE INCIDENTS OF UNINTENDED ACCELERATION, THE FIRST ONE AT 70 MILES AN HOUR ON A CROWDED FREEWAY, THE CAR JUMPED TO 80 MPH AND CONTINUED TO ACCELERATE, I TOOK OUT 200' OF SHRUBS ALONG THE FREEWAY & WAS LUCKY I COULD GET OFF THE FREEWAY AND STANDING ON THE BRAKE THE CAR FINALLY WENT TO IDLE.  THE AUTO SHOP CLEANED THE THROTTLE. 3 WEEKS LATER IT HAPPENED AGAIN AT 50 MPH, IN BOTH CASES I WAS LUCKY TO SURVIVE.  TOWED THE CAR TO F AIRFIELD HONDA, WHERE THEY HAD HONDA INSPECTORS CHECK OUT THE CAR.  THEY USED THE SAME EXCUSE AS TOYOTA SEVERAL YEARS AGO, THE FLOOR MATS WERE UNDER THE GAS PEDDLE.  THE CAR WAS NEVER DRIVEN WITH THE MATS UNDER THE GAS PEDDLE, IT WAS NOT LIKE THAT AT THE DEALER,  IT WOULD BE HARD TO DO WITH THE STEM OF THE GAS PEDDLE GOING UP INTO CHASSIS, AND NOT DOWN INTO FLOOR.  THEY SAID NOTHING WRONG, AND WOULD NOT TELL ME WHAT, IF ANYTHING, THEY DID TO FIX THE PROBLEM.  I SPENT ONE MONTH TRYING TO GET RESULTS OR RESOLUTION.  I WOULD NOT DRIVE THE CAR UNDER THESE CONDITIONS, NOR HAVE ANYONE I KNEW DRIVE IT.

TL* THE CONTACT OWNS A 1997 ACURA INTEGRA. THE CONTACT STATED THAT THE SPEEDOMETER WAS INOPERATIVE.  THE DEALER WAS CONTACTED, BUT WAS UNABLE TO DIAGNOSE THE FAILURE. THE MANUFACTURER WAS NOT NOTIFIED OF THE FAILURE. THE FAILURE MILEAGE WAS 84,779 AND THE CURRENT MILEAGE WAS 85,000.

CAR WAS PARKED FOR ABOUT 4 HOURS.  STARTED CAR AND IT STARTED TO OVERHEAT AND MAKE NOISE SO IGNITION KEY WAS TURNED OFF AND REMOVED.  CAR CONTINUE TO RUN, OVERHEAT AND MAKE NOISE.  FIRE DEPARTMENT WAS CALLED AND STALLED CAR WITH CLUTCH AND DISCONNECTED BATTERY.  OVERFLOW HOSE FROM RADIATOR HAD MELTED. *TR

TL*- THE CONTACT'S  SON WAS DRIVING  THE  1997 ACURA INTEGRA IN THE EVENING HOURS GOING AROUND THE OFF RAMP OF THE EXPRESSWAY.  THE DRIVER STATED THAT THE STEERING WHEEL LOCKED  AND HE WAS NOT ABLE TO CONTROL, AND THE VEHICLE AND HIT AN EMBANKMENT OFF THE EXPRESSWAY.  THE CONTACT WAS CONCERNED THAT THE AIR BAGS DIDN'T DEPLOY.  THE VEHICLE WAS TRAVELING AT  25 MPH WHICH WAS THE SPEED LIMIT, AND THAT IT HAD DRIZZLED.  HE FELT THAT THE AIR BAGS SHOULD HAVE DEPLOYED, AND IT WOULD HAVE SAVED THE DRIVER FROM SOME OF THE INJURIES THAT HE SUSTAINED.  THE DRIVER HAD NECK, LOWER BACK  AND HEAD INJURIES.  THE CONTACT WILL SUBMIT PICTURES ALONG WITH  POLICE  AND INSURANCE COMPANY  REPORTS.  THE CONTACT STATED THAT THE POLICE OFFICER STATED THAT THE LOW PROFILE TIRES WERE WORN  OUT ON THE INSIDE, BUT THE TIRES WERE ABOUT THREE MONTHS.  THE FAILURE MILEAGE WAS 11,300.*AK
SRS LIGHT CAME ON FOR NO REASON.  SERVICE CENTER AT ACURA DEALERSHIP INDICATED THAT THE SRS CONTROL UNIT HAD FAILED, AND REQUIRED REPLACEMENT.

WHILE THE VEHICLE WAS  PARKED CONSUMER NOTICED THAT THE SRS LIGHT APPEARED ON THE DASHBOARD AND REMAINED ON.  VEHICLE WAS TAKEN TO THE DEALER FOR INSPECTION, AND  MECHANIC DETERMINED THAT THE SRS CONTROL MODULE NEEDED TO BE REPLACED.   *AK

GAS TANK OF OUR 1997 ACURA INTEGRA DEVELOPED A LEAK AT THE SEAM. NO CORROSION NOTED. NO DAMAGE TO TANK HAD OCCURRED. THE CAR IS IN OVERALL GOOD CONDITION. THERE ARE NO PENDING RECALLS OR COMPLAINTS FOR THIS MAKE/MODEL THAT WE COULD LOCATE. THIS SEEMS LIKE AN UNUSUAL AND UNSAFE OCCURRENCE. WE HAVE NO OPTIONS (ACCORDING TO THE DEALER OR ACURA'S NATIONAL OFFICE) BUT TO REPLACE THE TANK AT A COST OF $900 PLUS.  *LA

1997 ACURA INTEGRA STALLS WITHOUT WARNING. THIS HAS HAPPENED ON 5 OCCASSIONS, TWICE ON THE FREEWAY. THE VEHICLE STARTS IMMEDIATELY AFTER THE STALL. I CHECKED THE MANUFACTURER RECALL LIST BUT THIS VEHICLE WAS ONLY RECALLED BY THE MALAYSIAN DOH AND NOT BY AMERICAN HONDA. IT WAS MANUFACTURED DURING THE 1996 TO 1999 RECALL TIMEFRAME FOR THE RECALL TO APPLY TO THIS VEHICLE.

WHILE TRAVELING AT HIGHWAY SPEEDS THE MOON ROOF, OR SUNROOF TOP FLEW OFF ONTO THE HIGHWAY.  CONSUMER STATES ROOF ALMOST HIT ANOTHER CAR.  CONSUMER FEELS IT MAY BE A MANUFACTURES DEFECT. PLEASE PROVIDE ANY FURTHER INFORMATION. TS
NO SUMMARY.  DT
WHILE DRIVING 75MPH SUN ROOF GLASS  BLEWOUT & BROKE. AT TIME OF MISHAP SUN ROOF WAS CLOSED.  *AK
CONSUMER WAS INVOLVED IN TWO COLLISIONS IN WHICH  DRIVER/OR PASSENGER'S AIR BAGS DID NOT DEPLOY.  PLEASE GIVE ANY FURTHER DETAILS.  *AK
CONSUMER WAS INVOLVED IN TWO COLLISIONS IN WHICH THE DRIVER'S OR PASSENGER'S AIR BAGS DID NOT DEPLOY CAUSE UNKNOWN.  *AK

DRIVING AT A SPEED OF 40MPH,WHEN EXITING FROM HWY,APPLYING BRAKES, BRAKE PEDAL WENT TO THE FLOOR WITH NO BACK PRESSURE ON BRAKE PEDAL AND CAR WAS NOT SLOWING DOWN, REAR ENDING A STOP CAR. AFTER HITTING THE STOP CAR, BRAKES WERE BEGINNING TO WORK AGAIN.

WINSTON TIRE CO. REPLACED BRAKE PADS AND COMPLETED BRAKE MAINTENANCE ON 7/6/98.  WE HAVE BEEN ADVISED THAT A FAULTY BRAKE PAD BECAME SEPARATED FROM ITS METAL BACKING, JAMMING INTO THE ROTOR WHICH SHATTERED AND RESULTED IN A LOSS OF STEERING, CAUSING THE VEHICLE TO "360" AND SLAM INTO A CURB.

THE FRONT PASSENGER SEAT BELT ANCHOR SLIDES IN AND CLICKS AS THOUGH IT WERE SECURE.  WHEN ANY AMOUNT OF PRESSURE IS APPLIED TO THE BELT, THE BELT COMES OUT OF THE ANCHOR.  THE VEHICLE HAS A PASSENGER SIDE AIRBAG AND THE BELT DOES NOT WORK.  THIS COULD CAUSE SERIOUS INJURY OR DEATH IN AN ACCIDENT OR FAULTY DISCHARGE OF THE AIRBAG.
REAR LEFT TIRE HAD BULGING SIDEWALL, AND APPEARED TO BLOW OUT. YH
MOON ROOF MOTOR FAILED.  NLM
IGNITION ASSEMBLY INTERLOCK FAILED, KEY CAN BE REMOVED FROM THE IGNITION WITHOUT PLACING THE TRANSMISSION IN PARK.

issues.title: Door Handle Mechanism Failure
issues.description: The exterior door handles, particularly on the driver's side, are prone to breaking internally. The plastic mechanism inside the handle can crack or fail, making it difficult or impossible to open the door from the outside.
symptoms: Must use interior handle to exit
issues.fix_description: Replace the entire door handle assembly with OEM or aftermarket parts. Some owners fabricate reinforcement plates for temporary fixes.
issues.prevention: Gentle operation of door handles, avoid yanking or excessive force, regular lubrication of mechanism

issues.title: Timing Chain Tensioner Wear
issues.description: The B18C5 engine's timing chain tensioner can wear out over time, causing chain slack and potential timing issues. This is particularly common on higher mileage engines and can lead to poor performance or engine damage.
symptoms: Rattling noise from engine on startup
issues.fix_description: Replace timing chain tensioner, timing chain, and related guides. Often done as a complete timing service.
issues.prevention: Regular oil changes with proper viscosity, avoid extended high RPM operation when engine is cold

issues.title: VTEC Solenoid Failure
issues.description: The VTEC solenoid can fail or become clogged, preventing the VTEC system from engaging properly. This results in poor high-RPM performance and loss of the characteristic VTEC power band.
issues.fix_description: Clean or replace VTEC solenoid, replace oil pressure switch if necessary, ensure proper oil pressure
issues.prevention: Regular oil changes, use proper oil viscosity, avoid running engine low on oil

issues.title: Clutch Master Cylinder Failure
issues.description: The clutch master cylinder can develop internal seals failure, leading to clutch fluid leaks and eventual clutch pedal failure. This is a safety issue as it can leave the driver unable to disengage the clutch.
issues.fix_description: Replace clutch master cylinder and slave cylinder, bleed clutch hydraulic system completely
issues.prevention: Regular clutch fluid changes, inspect for leaks periodically, avoid riding the clutch

issues.title: Rear Shock Mount Deterioration
issues.description: The rear shock tower mounts can deteriorate or crack over time, particularly on cars that have seen track use or aggressive driving. This affects handling and can cause noise.
issues.fix_description: Reinforce or replace shock tower mounts, may require welding or aftermarket reinforcement plates
issues.prevention: Avoid excessive track use without proper reinforcement, regular suspension inspections

issues.title: Distributor O-Ring Leak
issues.description: The O-ring seal around the distributor housing commonly fails, allowing oil to leak onto the engine and potentially causing ignition issues if oil contacts ignition components.
issues.fix_description: Replace distributor O-ring seal, clean affected areas thoroughly
issues.prevention: Regular inspection of distributor area, prompt replacement when leakage is noticed

issues.title: Window Regulator Failure
issues.description: Power window regulators, particularly on the driver's side, can fail causing windows to drop unexpectedly or become inoperable. The window motor or regulator mechanism typically fails.
symptoms: Window won't go up or down
issues.fix_description: Replace window regulator assembly and/or window motor, may require door panel removal
issues.prevention: Avoid forcing windows, keep window tracks clean and lubricated

issues.title: Fuel Injector Clogging
issues.description: The high-flow fuel injectors in the B18C5 engine can become clogged or develop inconsistent spray patterns, leading to rough idle, misfires, and poor fuel economy.
issues.fix_description: Professional fuel injector cleaning or replacement, fuel system cleaning
issues.prevention: Use quality fuel, regular fuel system cleaning, fuel filter replacement

issues.title: CV Joint Wear
issues.description: CV joints, particularly outer joints, wear out due to the aggressive driving nature of Type R ownership and the car's performance capabilities. Worn CV joints create clicking noises and vibration.
issues.fix_description: Replace worn CV joints or entire axle assembly, inspect CV boots for damage
issues.prevention: Avoid hard launches and aggressive cornering, regular CV boot inspection

issues.title: Throttle Position Sensor Failure
issues.description: The throttle position sensor can fail or provide inconsistent readings, causing erratic idle, poor throttle response, and potential stalling issues.
issues.fix_description: Replace throttle position sensor, clean throttle body, reset ECU adaptation
issues.prevention: Keep throttle body clean, avoid contaminated fuel

issues.title: Brake Master Cylinder Seal Failure
issues.description: The brake master cylinder seals can deteriorate over time, leading to brake fluid leaks and potential brake system failure. This is a critical safety issue.
issues.fix_description: Replace brake master cylinder, bleed entire brake system, inspect brake lines
issues.prevention: Regular brake fluid changes, inspect brake system annually

issues.title: Radiator Cap Pressure Loss
issues.description: The radiator cap seal can deteriorate, causing cooling system pressure loss and potential overheating issues. This is particularly common on track-driven cars.
issues.fix_description: Replace radiator cap, pressure test cooling system
issues.prevention: Replace radiator cap preventatively every few years, especially for track cars

editorial.tagline: The ultimate front-drive weapon for purists
editorial.hero_blurb: The Integra Type R stands as Honda's most focused performance machine ever built for American shores. This is what happens when Japanese engineers are given free rein to build the perfect front-wheel drive sports car.
editorial.essence: The Type R represents Honda's uncompromising pursuit of lightweight performance perfection. Every component was scrutinized, lightened, and optimized to create a naturally aspirated masterpiece that rewards skill and dedication.
editorial.heritage: Born from Honda's Type R philosophy established with the NSX-R, the Integra Type R brought track-focused engineering to the accessible sport compact segment. Only 3,823 examples reached American shores between 1997-2001, making it an instant collectible.
editorial.design_philosophy: Function over form defined every decision - from the deleted rear wiper to the minimalist interior. Honda's engineers prioritized weight reduction, structural rigidity, and aerodynamic efficiency to create the ultimate driver's tool.
editorial.motorsport_history: Dominated SCCA racing and became the benchmark for front-drive track weapons. The Type R's success in amateur and professional motorsport cemented its reputation as a giant-killer capable of embarrassing much more expensive machinery.
editorial.engine_character: The B18C5 is a high-strung thoroughbred that demands respect. It builds power linearly until VTEC engagement at 5,600 RPM, then transforms into a screaming banshee that pulls hard to its 8,400 RPM redline.
editorial.transmission_feel: The close-ratio 5-speed transmission offers crisp, mechanical shifts with short throws. Each gear change feels precise and deliberate, connecting driver to machine through perfectly weighted shift action.
editorial.chassis_dynamics: Razor-sharp handling with minimal body roll and telepathic responses to steering inputs. The suspension is firmly damped but compliant enough for street use, though track work reveals its true potential.
editorial.steering_feel: Unassisted rack-and-pinion steering provides pure, unfiltered feedback from the front wheels. Effort builds naturally with speed, offering perfect communication about grip levels and road surface conditions.
editorial.brake_confidence: Large Brembo calipers and discs provide fade-resistant stopping power with excellent pedal feel. Initial bite is strong, with linear progression that inspires confidence during aggressive driving.
editorial.sound_signature: The B18C5 produces an intoxicating high-pitched wail that intensifies dramatically above 6,000 RPM. The intake tract creates a distinctive induction roar that complements the exhaust's aggressive bark.
editorial.ideal_owner: Driving purists who value analog feedback over modern conveniences. Perfect for enthusiasts who understand that the best performance comes from lightweight simplicity and are willing to sacrifice comfort for connection.
editorial.not_ideal_for: Buyers seeking daily driver comfort, modern amenities, or effortless performance. The Type R demands active participation and rewards only those willing to work for its gifts.
editorial.buyers_summary: Prices have skyrocketed as collectors recognize the Type R's significance in automotive history. Find the cleanest, most original example possible - modifications often diminish rather than enhance this perfectly balanced machine.

expertReviews.title: Is the 2025 Acura Integra Type R the BEST new compact ...
pros: Increased horsepower to 375hp from stock 320hp
Over 200 pounds weight reduction with carbon fiber components
Excellent manual transmission described as one of the best gearboxes in modern era
Functional aerodynamic improvements with carbon fiber splitter and rear wing
Track-focused modifications including roll cage and adjustable suspension
Premium materials including Recaro carbon fiber bucket seats and Alcantara interior
cons: Estimated high price of $70,000-75,000 vs $53,000 for stock Type S
expertReviews.verdict: This heavily modified 2025 Acura Integra showcases HRC's racing expertise with significant performance upgrades including 375hp, 200+ pound weight reduction, and extensive track-focused modifications. While the estimated $70-75k price point is high, the reviewer is enthusiastic about the potential Type R variant and hopes Honda will produce it. The car demonstrates strong connection between Honda's racing technology and street applications.

expertReviews.title: Acura Integra Type R | The BEST Sport Compact of All Time?
pros: Iconic design with perfect 90s JDM styling
Extremely rare and appreciating in value (over six figures now)
Exceptional manual transmission with titanium shift knob
Low dashboard and thin A-pillars provide excellent visibility
Aggressive bolstered seats with red contrast stitching
Simple, mechanical, easy-to-use controls
Only US-sold Acura with Type R badge making it truly special
Distinctive Phoenix Yellow color and Type R exterior badges
cons: Very cramped rear seating for only 4 passengers
No center rear seat or armrest
Frequently stolen due to high desirability
expertReviews.verdict: The 2001 Acura Integra Type R is described as one of the best sport compacts of all time, representing the pinnacle of the iconic DC2 generation. This particular example with only 6,520 miles is essentially a time capsule from Honda's collection. The reviewer emphasizes its legendary status, incredible appreciation in value, and timeless design that still looks amazing today. The car embodies 90s JDM culture with its distinctive styling, manual transmission, and driver-focused interior.

expertReviews.title: Why the 2001 Acura Integra Type R Is STILL the ULTIMATE FWD Performance Car
pros: 195 horsepower VTEC twin cam 4-cylinder
5-speed manual with perfect gating
Sharp steering and great sight lines
Lightweight at just over 2,500 lbs
Stripped down simplicity
Ultimate front-wheel drive performance
expertReviews.verdict: The 2001 Acura Integra Type R represents the ultimate peak of front-wheel drive performance with its screaming VTEC engine, perfect manual transmission, and lightweight stripped-down design. No modern car can match its pure driving dynamics and focused approach to performance.

expertReviews.title: 1998 Acura Integra Type R - POV Driving Impressions
pros: VTEC engine is intoxicating
Telepathic manual transmission with perfect rev matching
Exceptional visibility and greenhouse design
Lightweight and well-balanced chassis
Surprisingly comfortable and livable
Excellent mechanical feedback
Great low-down torque for a 1.8L
Perfect gear spacing to keep in VTEC
No rattles or vibrations despite age
Near perfect calibration from Honda
cons: Limited mechanical grip with stock tires
High RPM at highway speeds (4000+ at 75mph)
expertReviews.verdict: Described as 'one of the best cars ever driven' and 'dare near perfect' by the reviewers. The Integra Type R showcases Honda's racing influence with exceptional manual transmission feel, VTEC engine character, and balanced chassis dynamics. The only suggested improvement would be stickier tires. Considered an iconic driver's car that maintains Honda's driving magic.

expertReviews.title: Can the new Acura Integra keep up with its peers? Or the original Type R?  Cammisa Drag Race Replay
pros: Short gears make it feel quick in real world driving
Feels quick in first and second gear
Beat the legendary Integra Type R in drag race
cons: Most expensive car in comparison but slowest performance
1.2 seconds behind Elantra N in quarter mile
Can't keep up with Jetta GLI or Hyundai Elantra N
expertReviews.verdict: The new Integra is completely outclassed by its competitors despite being the most expensive. While it beats the legendary Type R and feels quick due to short gearing, it's significantly slower than both the Hyundai Elantra N and VW Jetta GLI in straight-line performance. The 1.5L engine decision proves to be a major disadvantage against the 2.0L competition.

expertReviews.title: Is the 2024 Acura Integra Type S a BETTER performance car than a Civic Type R?
pros: 320 horsepower and 310 lb-ft of torque (5 more hp than Civic Type R)
2.8 inches wider than standard Integra with flared fenders for better grip
Six-speed manual transmission with limited slip differential
High-quality interior with heated seats and premium materials
Unique NSX-inspired wheel design and aggressive exterior styling
Functional aerodynamic features including heat extractor and front air intakes
Triple-tip exhaust with pops and bangs sound
265-width Michelin Pilot Sport 4S tires all around
Adaptive dampers and Brembo brakes with 13.8-inch rotors
cons: No data logging system like Civic Type R has
Some gloss black interior trim elements
expertReviews.verdict: The 2024 Acura Integra Type S appears to be a compelling alternative to the Honda Civic Type R, offering slightly more power, unique styling with aggressive flared fenders, and premium interior touches. While it lacks some track-focused features like data logging, it provides a more street-oriented luxury performance experience. The reviewer suggests it may satisfy Honda fans who wanted a more aggressive design than the FL5 Civic Type R received.
